  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/smartphones/\" rel=\"tag\">智能手机</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/03/19/flappy-bird-returns/\"><img alt=\"An employee plays the game Flappy Bird at a smartphone store in Hanoi on February 10, 2014.  The Vietnamese developer behind the smash-hit free game Flappy Bird has pulled his creation from online stores after announcing that its runaway success had ruined his \" src=\"http://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/adam/17fd9896fc9b1c6c908163c6bf4b1fa6/468281287.jpeg\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n在这个年头只有很少又简单、又复古、又受欢迎而又免费的游戏了，但早前大受欢迎而又被开发者 Dong Nguyen 下架的 Flappy Bird 却是其中一款。早前他因为受不了来自公众和传媒的「压力」而放弃每日五万美元的广告费。之后，早阵之在一个 Rolling Stone 的访问中他却指出正在考虑给 Flappy Bird 重新的机会，而答案亦跟预期一样 -- 他现在决定给这只小鸟重新的机会了。这个公布是他在响应 Twitter follower 之时给出，虽然没有详细指出其复活的详情是如何，但却表示不会在不久的将来发生而已。到底 Nguyen 是不是有什么秘密的新元素要加入 Flappy Bird，然后才让牠再跟大家见面呢？<br />\n<br />\n[图片来源：Getty]<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/03/19/flappy-bird-returns/\">Engadget</a>、<a href=\"https://www.yahoo.com/tech/die-another-day-flappy-bird-lives-80081921563.html\">Yahoo</a><br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"https://twitter.com/dongatory/statuses/446308190984998912\">Dong Nguyen（Twitter）</a></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/03/19/flappy-bird-returns/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20853299/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/03/19/flappy-bird-returns/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
